#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This settings module configures &plasma;'s power management service, also "
"known as PowerDevil. It allows you to make trade-offs between saving energy "
"and making full use of your system's capabilities. The power management "
"service is integrated into your desktop and can interact with your hardware."
msgstr ""
"Ta modul z nastavitvami konfigurira storitev upravljanja porabe energije v "
"programu &plasma;, znan tudi kot PowerDevil. Omogoča vam, da izbirate med "
"varčevanjem z energijo in polnim izkoriščanjem zmogljivosti sistema. "
"Storitev upravljanja energije je integrirana v vaše namizje in lahko "
"komunicira z vašo strojno opremo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:34
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The module's main page shows settings that can help to save energy. Only the "
"settings that are supported by your system will be shown. On battery-powered "
"systems, the page provides three tabs with different settings for "
"<guilabel>On AC Power</guilabel>, <guilabel>On Battery</guilabel>, and "
"<guilabel>On Low Battery</guilabel> power states."
msgstr ""
"Glavna stran modula prikazuje nastavitve, ki lahko pomagajo pri varčevanju z "
"energijo. Prikazane bodo samo nastavitve, ki jih podpira vaš sistem. V "
"sistemih, ki se napajajo iz baterij, stran ponuja tri zavihke z različnimi "
"nastavitvami za stanja napajanja <guilabel>Na izmenični tok</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>Na baterijo</guilabel> in <guilabel>Pri nizko napolnjeni bateriji</"
"guilabel>."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:39
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Power Management Settings</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Nastavitve upravljanja z energijo</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:45
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Power Management Settings</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Nastavitve upravljanja z energijo</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:48
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Power Management Settings</para>"
msgstr "<para>Nastavitve upravljanja z energijo</para>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:55
#, no-c-format
msgid "Suspend Session"
msgstr "Prekini sejo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:56
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are common circumstances where you expect the system to sleep, shut "
"down, or pause your regular desktop session in other ways. This section "
"allows you to define how exactly your system will behave in these "
"circumstances."
msgstr ""
"V pogostih okoliščinah pričakujete, da se bo sistem preklopil v stanje "
"mirovanja, se izklopil ali na druge načine začasno ustavil vašo običajno "
"sejo namizja. V tem razdelku lahko določite, kako se bo vaš sistem obnašal v "
"teh okoliščinah."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:62
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do nothing"
msgstr "Ne naredi ničesar"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "Carry on with your desktop session as if nothing happened."
msgstr "Nadaljuj s sejo namizja, kot da se ni nič zgodilo."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:69
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sleep"
msgstr "Zaspi"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Save power and wake up quickly. Many hardware components enter a power-"
"saving state without fully shutting down the system. Unsaved data will be "
"lost if the power supply gets interrupted&#x2014;for example when the "
"battery is fully depleted. The degree of power savings achieved while "
"sleeping depends on hardware and firmware provided by the system "
"manufacturer."
msgstr ""
"Prihrani energijo in se hitro prebudi. Številne strojne komponente preidejo "
"v stanje varčevanja z energijo, ne da bi popolnoma izklopile sistem. "
"Neshranjeni podatki bodo izgubljeni, če se napajanje prekine&#x2014; na "
"primer, ko je baterija popolnoma izpraznjena. Stopnja prihranka energije, "
"doseženega med spanjem, je odvisna od strojne in vdelane programske opreme, "
"ki jo zagotavlja proizvajalec sistema."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The module provides an additional drop-down setting to select the exact "
"sleep mode to enter when \"Sleep\" is activated:"
msgstr ""
"Modul ponuja dodatno spustno nastavitev za izbiro natančnega načina "
"mirovanja, v katerega naj sistem vstopi, ko je aktiviran način \"Spanje\":"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:76
#, no-c-format
msgid "Standby"
msgstr "V stanju pripravljenosti"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Save the current desktop session to memory. This traditional sleep mode "
"enters sleep quickly and wakes up quickly. Battery-powered systems are often "
"designed to last anywhere between a day and 1-2 weeks in this state. Also "
"known as \"Suspend to RAM\"."
msgstr ""
"Shrani trenutno sejo namizja v pomnilnik. Ta tradicionalni način mirovanja "
"hitro preklopi v stanje spanja in se hitro prebudi. Sistemi, ki se napajajo "
"z baterijami, so pogosto zasnovani tako, da v tem stanju zdržijo od enega "
"dneva do enega-dveh tednov. Znano tudi kot \"Suspend to RAM\"."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid "Hybrid sleep"
msgstr "Hibridno spanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Save the current desktop session to both memory and a storage drive, such as "
"an SSD or hard drive. Waking up is quick like standby, but unsaved data will "
"survive even if power runs out while sleeping. As a downside, this sleep "
"mode puts the most strain on your storage drive, which potentially reduces "
"its longevity and takes longer for the system to start sleeping compared to "
"using standby. Also known as \"Hybrid suspend\"."
msgstr ""
"Shrani trenutno sejo namizja v pomnilnik in na pogon za shranjevanje, kot je "
"SSD ali trdi disk. Prebujanje je hitro kot v stanju pripravljenosti, vendar "
"se neshranjeni podatki ohranijo, tudi če med spanjem zmanjka napajanja. "
"Slaba stran tega načina mirovanja je, da ta način mirovanja najbolj obremeni "
"pogon za shranjevanje, kar lahko skrajša njegovo življenjsko dobo in traja "
"dlje, da sistem preklopi v stanje pripravljenosti, v primerjavi z uporabo "
"stanja pripravljenosti. Znano tudi kot \"hibridno stanje pripravljenosti - "
"hybrid suspend\"."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "Standby, then hibernate"
msgstr "Stanje pripravljenosti, nato mirovanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enter standby mode initially, then hibernate after a period of inactivity. "
"If the system only sleeps for a while, this sleep mode provides the quick "
"wake-up times and storage drive longevity benefits of regular standby. If "
"the system remains inactive for a longer amount of time, hibernation reduces "
"power consumption even further and ensures that unsaved data is not lost. "
"The amount of time until hibernation is defined by your low-level system "
"configuration. Also known as \"Suspend, then hibernate\"."
msgstr ""
"Najprej preklopi v stanje pripravljenosti, nato pa po obdobju neaktivnosti "
"preklopi v stanje spanja. Če sistem spi le nekaj časa, ta način mirovanja "
"zagotavlja prednosti hitrega prebujanja in daljše življenjske dobe pogona za "
"shranjevanje, ki jih zagotavlja običajni način pripravljenosti. Če sistem "
"ostane neaktiven dlje časa, stanje mirovanja še dodatno zmanjša porabo "
"energije in zagotovi, da se neshranjeni podatki ne izgubijo. Čas do stanja "
"mirovanja je določen z nizkonivojsko konfiguracijo sistema. Znano tudi kot "
"\"Zaustavitev, nato mirovanje - Suspend, then hibernate\"."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:96
#, no-c-format
msgid "Hibernate"
msgstr "Mirovanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:98
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Save the current desktop session to your storage drive and power off. "
"Hibernating and restoring the session takes longer than sleep in standby "
"mode, but unsaved data will not be lost if the power supply gets "
"interrupted. Hibernation is widely supported across different kinds of "
"hardware, as long as your storage drive is set up with a large enough swap "
"partition to store the contents of your system memory. Also known as "
"\"Suspend to disk\"."
msgstr ""
"Shrani trenutno sejo namizja na pogon za shranjevanje in izklopi. Preklop v "
"mirovanje in obnovitev seje trajata dlje kot spanje v stanju "
"pripravljenosti, vendar neshranjeni podatki ne bodo izgubljeni, če pride do "
"prekinitve napajanja. Preklop v mirovanje je široko podprt v različnih "
"vrstah strojne opreme, če je bil vaš pogon za shranjevanje nastavljen z "
"dovolj veliko izmenjalno particijo za shranjevanje vsebine sistemskega "
"pomnilnika. Znano tudi kot \"Zaustavitev na disk - Suspend to disk\"."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:103
#, no-c-format
msgid "Shut down"
msgstr "Zaustavitev"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:105
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Log out of your desktop session and any other open sessions, then power off "
"the system. Open applications will ask to save any unsaved data before "
"closing. For future sessions, application state is only restored to the "
"extent that the application itself supports it."
msgstr ""
"Odjavi se iz namizne seje in vseh drugih odprtih sej, nato pa izklopi "
"sistem. Odprte aplikacije bodo pred zaprtjem zahtevale shranjevanje "
"morebitnih neshranjenih podatkov. V prihodnjih sejah se stanje aplikacije "
"obnovi le, če aplikacija sama to podpira."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid "Lock screen"
msgstr "Zakleni zaslon"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:112
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Lock the screen without reducing power consumption. To save power while also "
"locking the screen, select \"Sleep\" or \"Hibernate\" and ensure that "
"locking after waking from sleep is enabled in the Screen Locking settings "
"module. Note that the Screen Locking module provides a separate setting for "
"locking after a period of inactivity, so this is only available as a power "
"button or laptop lid action."
msgstr ""
"Zaklene zaslon brez zmanjšanja porabe energije. Če želite prihraniti "
"energijo in hkrati zakleniti zaslon, izberite \"Zaspi\" ali \"V mirovanje\" "
"in se prepričajte, da je v modulu nastavitev zaklepanja zaslona omogočeno "
"zaklepanje po prebujanju iz stanja pripravljenosti. Upoštevajte, da modul "
"zaklepanja zaslona ponuja ločeno nastavitev za zaklepanje po določenem "
"obdobju neaktivnosti, zato je to na voljo le kot dejanje gumba za vklop ali "
"pokrova prenosnika."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:117
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show logout screen"
msgstr "Prikaži zaslon za odjavo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:119
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Present a dialog with options to sleep, hibernate, shut down or log out. "
"This is only available as an option when pressing the system's physical "
"power button."
msgstr ""
"Prikaži pogovorno okno z možnostmi za spanje, mirovanje, izklop ali odjavo. "
"Ta možnost je na voljo le ob pritisku fizičnega gumba za vklop/izklop "
"sistema."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:124 index.docbook:158
#, no-c-format
msgid "Turn off screen"
msgstr "Izklopi zaslon"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:126
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Fade to black and turn off the display backlight. The \"Display and "
"Brightness\" section has its own setting for turning off the screen, "
"independent of the inactivity action configured in \"Suspend Session\"."
msgstr ""
"Zatemnitev in izklop osvetlitve ozadja zaslona. Razdelek \"Zaslon in svetlost"
"\" ima svojo nastavitev za izklop zaslona ​​neodvisno od dejanja neaktivnosti, "
"konfiguriranega v \"Prekinitev seje\"."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:135
#, no-c-format
msgid "Display and Brightness"
msgstr "Zaslon in svetlost"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:136
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Laptop displays and keyboard backlights account for much of the power draw "
"of an otherwise idle laptop. Large monitors often draw more power than an "
"entire laptop including its display. Certain kinds of displays are "
"susceptible to burn-in or stuck pixels depending on the usage pattern. For "
"all of these reasons, it helps to reduce brightness or turn off displays and "
"backlights altogether if they're not needed."
msgstr ""
"Zasloni prenosnikov in osvetlitev ozadja tipkovnice predstavljajo velik del "
"porabe energije sicer nedejavnega prenosnika. Veliki monitorji pogosto "
"porabijo več energije kot celoten prenosnik, vključno z zaslonom. Nekatere "
"vrste zaslonov so dovzetne za vžgane ali zataknjene slikovne pike, odvisno "
"od vzorca uporabe. Zaradi vseh teh razlogov je priporočljivo zmanjšati "
"svetlost ali popolnoma izklopiti zaslone in osvetlitev ozadja, če jih ne "
"potrebujete."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:142
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Change screen brightness</guilabel> / <guilabel>Change keyboard "
"brightness</guilabel>"
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Sprememba svetlosti zaslona</guilabel> / <guilabel>Sprememba "
"svetlosti tipkovnice</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Define a brightness level to set when switching between <guilabel>On AC "
"Power</guilabel>, <guilabel>On Battery</guilabel>, and <guilabel>On Low "
"Battery</guilabel> power states."
msgstr ""
"Določite raven svetlosti, ki jo želite nastaviti pri preklapljanju med "
"stanji napajanja <guilabel>Na izmenični tok</guilabel>, <guilabel>Na "
"baterijo</guilabel> in <guilabel>Pri nizko napolnjeni bateriji</guilabel>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:146
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Screen and keyboard brightness can also be changed on the fly through the "
"<guilabel>Brightness &amp;amp; Color</guilabel> applet, as well as with "
"keyboard shortcuts. Changing brightness on the fly will not affect the "
"settings in this module. If no brightness level is set in this settings "
"module, the brightness will remain the same when switching between power "
"states."
msgstr ""
"Svetlost zaslona in tipkovnice lahko spreminjate tudi sproti prek programčka "
"<guilabel>Svetlost in barva</guilabel>, pa tudi s bližnjicami na tipkovnici. "
"Sprotno spreminjanje svetlosti ne bo vplivalo na nastavitve v tem modulu. Če "
"v tem modulu z nastavitvami ni nastavljene nobene ravni svetlosti, bo "
"svetlost ostala enaka pri preklapljanju med stanji napajanja."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:151
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dim automatically"
msgstr "Samodejno zatemni"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:153
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Reduce screen brightness after a period of inactivity. When user activity is "
"detected again, the screen will return to its previous brightness level."
msgstr ""
"Zmanjšaj svetlost zaslona po obdobju neaktivnosti. Ko je uporabnikova "
"aktivnost ponovno zaznana, se bo svetlost zaslona vrnila na prejšnjo raven."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:160
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Fade to black and turn off the display backlight after a period of "
"inactivity. When user activity is detected again, the screen will turn on "
"again. A shorter wait time can be set for when the screen locker is active."
msgstr ""
"Po določenem času neaktivnosti se osvetlitev zaslona nato zatemni in "
"izklopi. Ko uporabnik znova zazna svojo aktivnost, se zaslon znova vklopi. "
"Za aktivno zaklepanje zaslona je mogoče nastaviti krajši čas čakanja."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:169
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other Settings"
msgstr "Druge nastavitve"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:173
#, no-c-format
msgid "Switch to power profile"
msgstr "Preklopi na profil napajanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:175
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Define system performance characteristics to set when switching between "
"<guilabel>On AC Power</guilabel>, <guilabel>On Battery</guilabel>, and "
"<guilabel>On Low Battery</guilabel> power states. A power profile such as "
"<guilabel>Power Save</guilabel>, <guilabel>Balanced</guilabel> and "
"<guilabel>Performance</guilabel> allows you to trade off performance vs. "
"power consumption, which also affects the levels of heat and fan noise your "
"system will produce."
msgstr ""
"Določi značilnosti delovanja sistema, ki jih želite nastaviti pri "
"preklapljanju med stanji napajanja <guilabel>Napajanje iz izmeničnega toka</"
"guilabel>, <guilabel>Na baterijo</guilabel> in <guilabel>Pri nizki "
"napolnjenosti baterije</guilabel>. Profil napajanja, kot so "
"<guilabel>Varčevanje z energijo</guilabel>, <guilabel>Uravnoteženo</"
"guilabel> in <guilabel>Zmogljivo delovanje</guilabel>, vam omogoča, da "
"uskladite zmogljivost delovanja s porabo energije, kar vpliva tudi na raven "
"toplote in hrupa ventilatorja, ki ga bo proizvajal vaš sistem."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:177
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Power profiles can also be changed on the fly through the <guilabel>Power "
"&amp;amp; Battery</guilabel> applet, as well as with keyboard shortcuts. "
"Changing power profiles on the fly will not affect the settings in this "
"module. If no brightness level is set in this settings module, the "
"brightness will remain the same when switching between power states."
msgstr ""
"Profile porabe energije lahko sproti spreminjate tudi prek programčka "
"<guilabel>Napajanje in baterija</guilabel> ali s bližnjicami na tipkovnici. "
"Spreminjanje profilov porabe energije sproti ne bo vplivalo na nastavitve v "
"tem modulu. Če v tem modulu z nastavitvami ni nastavljene nobene ravni "
"svetlosti, bo svetlost ostala enaka pri preklapljanju med stanji porabe "
"energije."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:182
#, no-c-format
msgid "Run Script"
msgstr "Zaženi skript"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:184
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configure a custom script to run when switching between <guilabel>On AC "
"Power</guilabel>, <guilabel>On Battery</guilabel>, and <guilabel>On Low "
"Battery</guilabel> power states, or after a period of inactivity."
msgstr ""
"Konfigurirajte skript po meri, ki se zažene ob preklapljanju med stanji "
"napajanja <guilabel>Na izmenični tok</guilabel>, <guilabel>Na baterijo</"
"guilabel> in <guilabel>Pri nizki napolnjenosti baterije</guilabel> ali po "
"obdobju neaktivnosti."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:193
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Advanced Power Settings</title>"
msgstr "<title>Napredne nastavitve napajanja</title>"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:196
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Advanced Power Settings</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Napredne nastavitve napajanja</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:202
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Advanced Power Settings</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Napredne nastavitve napajanja</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:205
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Advanced Power Settings</para>"
msgstr "<para>Napredne nastavitve napajanja</para>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:211
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open this page by pressing the button in the corner of the settings module's "
"main page."
msgstr ""
"To stran odprite s pritiskom na gumb v kotu glavne strani modula z "
"nastavitvami."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:216
#, no-c-format
msgid "Battery Levels"
msgstr "Ravni napolnjenosti baterije"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:218
#, no-c-format
msgid "These settings are only displayed on battery-powered systems."
msgstr ""
"Te nastavitve so prikazane samo na sistemih, ki se napajajo iz baterij."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:222
#, no-c-format
msgid "Low level"
msgstr "Nizka raven"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:224
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Below this percentage, the battery charge will be considered low. If the "
"system is unplugged, settings from the <guilabel>On Low Battery</guilabel> "
"profile will be used instead of <guilabel>On Battery</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Pod tem odstotkom se bo napolnjenost baterije štela za nizko. Če je sistem "
"izklopljen iz napajanja, bodo namesto profila <guilabel>Na baterijo</"
"guilabel> uporabljene nastavitve iz profila <guilabel>Pri nizki "
"napolnjenosti baterije</guilabel>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:228
#, no-c-format
msgid "Critical level"
msgstr "Kritična raven"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:230
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Below this percentage, the battery charge will be considered at a critical "
"level."
msgstr "Pod tem odstotkom se bo napolnjenost baterije štela za kritično raven."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:234
#, no-c-format
msgid "At critical level"
msgstr "Na kritični ravni"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:236
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Define the action that will be performed when the battery charge reaches the "
"critical level."
msgstr ""
"Določa dejanje, ki bo izvedeno, ko napolnjenost baterije doseže kritično "
"raven."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:240
#, no-c-format
msgid "Peripheral devices"
msgstr "Periferne naprave"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:242
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Below this percentage, the battery charge for peripheral devices &eg; a "
"wireless mouse will be considered low."
msgstr ""
"Pod tem odstotkom se bo napolnjenost baterije perifernih naprav, npr. "
"brezžične miške, štela za nizko."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:251
#, no-c-format
msgid "Charge Limit"
msgstr "Omejitev obremenitve"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:253
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These settings are only displayed if the system supports charge limits for "
"its battery."
msgstr ""
"Te nastavitve so prikazane le, če sistem podpira omejitve polnjenja baterije."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:256
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Regularly charging the battery close to 100% or fully discharging it close "
"to 0% can cause it to deteriorate faster. By limiting the maximum battery "
"charge, you can help extend your battery's lifespan."
msgstr ""
"Redno polnjenje baterije blizu 100 % ali popolno praznjenje blizu 0 % lahko "
"povzroči njeno hitrejšo obrabo. Z omejitvijo največje napolnjenosti baterije "
"lahko podaljšate življenjsko dobo baterije."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:259
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Different sources recommend different charge levels for lithium-ion "
"batteries. The general consensus among available research indicates that "
"keeping your battery within the 25%-75% range is optimal to retain its "
"capacity over the years. A range of 15%-85% still significantly increases "
"battery life compared to wider ranges."
msgstr ""
"Različni viri priporočajo različne stopnje napolnjenosti litij-ionskih "
"baterij. Splošno soglasje med razpoložljivimi raziskavami kaže, da je "
"ohranjanje kapacitete baterije v območju od 25% do 75% optimalno za vrsto "
"let. Območje od 15% do 85% še vedno znatno podaljša življenjsko dobo "
"baterije v primerjavi s širšimi območji."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:262
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that battery lifespan is mainly affected by its charge level over time, "
"more so than the number of charging and discharging cycles."
msgstr ""
"Upoštevajte, da na življenjsko dobo baterije vpliva predvsem njena "
"napolnjenost skozi čas, bolj kot število ciklov polnjenja in praznjenja."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:266
#, no-c-format
msgid "Stop charging at"
msgstr "Prenehaj polniti ob"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:268
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The upper charge limit for your battery. Once this level is reached, the "
"battery is considered fully charged and the system won't charge it any "
"further."
msgstr ""
"Zgornja meja napolnjenosti baterije. Ko je dosežena ta raven, se baterija "
"šteje za popolnoma napolnjeno in sistem je ne bo več polnil."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:272
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start charging once below"
msgstr "Začni polniti, ko je pod"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The lower charge limit. Once the battery discharges past this level, the "
"system will start charging it again. This can be a little lower than the "
"upper limit, or the same percentage to keep drawing power while the battery "
"charge remains constant."
msgstr ""
"Spodnja meja polnjenja. Ko se baterija izprazni prek te ravni, jo bo sistem "
"znova začel polniti. Ta je lahko nekoliko nižja od zgornje meje ali enak "
"odstotek, da se ohrani poraba energije, medtem ko napolnjenost baterije "
"ostane konstantna."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:280
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some systems require unplugging the power cable and reconnecting it before "
"the settings are respected. Some systems don't store charge limits when "
"powered off. Be aware of possible limitations."
msgstr ""
"Nekateri sistemi zahtevajo izklop in ponovni priklop napajalnega kabla, "
"preden se nastavitve uveljavijo. Nekateri sistemi ne shranjujejo omejitev "
"polnjenja, ko so izklopljeni. Bodite pozorni na morebitne omejitve."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:292
#, no-c-format
msgid "PowerDevil Runner"
msgstr "Zaganjalnik PowerDevil"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:294
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"PowerDevil can be manually controlled through &krunner; (<keycombo action="
"\"simul\">&Alt;<keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo>). This makes changing "
"brightness, power profile, and more much easier and faster. The runner has "
"various keywords you can enter to access its functions"
msgstr ""
"PowerDevil je mogoče ročno upravljati prek &krunner; (<keycombo action="
"\"simul\">&Alt;<keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo>). Tako je spreminjanje "
"profila, svetlosti, profila napajanja in še več veliko lažje in hitreje. "
"Runner ima različne ključne besede, ki jih lahko vnesete za dostop do "
"njegovih funkcij"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:297
#, no-c-format
msgid "Runner Keywords"
msgstr "Ključne besede zaganjalnika"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:298
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here comes a list of keywords you can enter in &krunner; to perform "
"PowerDevil related actions."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj je seznam ključnih besed, ki jih lahko vnesete v &krunner; za "
"izvajanje dejanj, povezanih s PowerDevilom."

#. Tag: userinput
#: index.docbook:302
#, no-c-format
msgid "power profile"
msgstr "profil moči"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:304
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can manually choose a power profile using this keyword. All available "
"profiles will be shown in form of &krunner; matches."
msgstr ""
"Profil moči lahko ročno izberete s to ključno besedo. Vsi razpoložljivi "
"profili bodo prikazani v obliki zadetkov &krunner;."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:309
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>screen brightness</userinput> or <userinput>dim screen</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>svetlost zaslona</userinput> ali <userinput>zatemnjen zaslon</"
"userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:311
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can control screen brightness through this keyword. In this form, some "
"&krunner; matches that let you run common power actions will be shown. If "
"you enter a value after the keyword (&eg;: <userinput>screen brightness 50</"
"userinput>), the brightness will be set to that value."
msgstr ""
"Svetlost zaslona lahko nadzorujete s to ključno besedo. V tem obrazcu bodo "
"prikazana nekatera ujemanja &krunner;, ki omogočajo izvajanje običajnih "
"dejanj za upravljanje napajanja. Če za ključno besedo vnesete vrednost "
"(npr.: <userinput>svetlost zaslona 50</userinput>), bo svetlost nastavljena "
"na to vrednost."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:316
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>suspend</userinput>, <userinput>sleep</userinput>, "
"<userinput>hibernate</userinput>, <userinput>to ram</userinput> or "
"<userinput>to disk</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>začasno prekini</userinput>, <userinput>spanje</userinput>, "
"<userinput>mirovanje</userinput>, <userinput>v ram</userinput> ali "
"<userinput>na disk</userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:319
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can set your computer into a low power mode through these keywords. "
"Available methods will be shown as &krunner; matches."
msgstr ""
"S temi ključnimi besedami lahko svoj računalnik nastavite v način nizke "
"porabe. Razpoložljive metode bodo prikazane kot &krunner; tekme."

#~ msgid "2016-08-26"
#~ msgstr "26.08.2016"

#~ msgid "PowerDevil, a Power Management Daemon"
#~ msgstr "PowerDevil, daemon za upravljanje porabe energije"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "This module is a configuration tool for managing Power Management in "
#~ "&plasma;. It is a configurator for the PowerDevil daemon."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Ta modul je konfiguracijsko orodje za upravljanje upravljanja porabe "
#~ "energije v &plasma;. Je konfigurator za daemon PowerDevil."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Through this module, you can define your computer's behavior in various "
#~ "situations, allowing you to save as much energy as possible."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "S tem modulom lahko določite obnašanje vašega računalnika v različnih "
#~ "situacijah, kar vam omogoča, da prihranite čim več energije."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Powerdevil works with Solid only and it's integrated in your desktop. You "
#~ "won't even notice it is running, apart from notifications. Moreover, "
#~ "Powerdevil checks your system capabilities first, so you'll see only "
#~ "options available for your system in this module."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Powerdevil deluje samo s programom Solid in je integriran v vaše namizje. "
#~ "Sploh ne boste opazili, da se izvaja, razen obvestil. Poleg tega "
#~ "Powerdevil najprej preveri zmogljivosti vašega sistema, tako da boste v "
#~ "tem modulu videli samo možnosti, ki so na voljo za vaš sistem."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Note that PowerDevil does not poll your system. This means that it will "
#~ "not waste energy while trying to save it, as some other power managers do."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Upoštevajte, da PowerDevil ne anketira vašega sistema. To pomeni, da ne "
#~ "bo zapravljal energije, medtem ko jo poskuša varčevati, kot to počnejo "
#~ "nekateri drugi upravljalniki energije."

#~ msgid "<title>Energy Saving Settings</title>"
#~ msgstr "<title>Nastavitve varčevanja z energijo</title>"

#~ msgid "There are a lot of options you can configure for each profile:"
#~ msgstr "Obstaja veliko možnosti, ki jih lahko konfigurirate za vsak profil:"

#~ msgid "Screen brightness"
#~ msgstr "Svetlost zaslona"

#~ msgid "Sets the screen's brightness using a slider."
#~ msgstr "Z drsnikom nastavi svetlost zaslona."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "If checked, the display will be progressively dimmed, until reaching "
#~ "brightness 0, in the amount of time you specify in the spin box."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Če je označeno, bo zaslon postopoma zatemnjen, dokler ne doseže svetlosti "
#~ "0, v času, ki ga določite v vrtilnem polju."

#~ msgid "Here you can set the timeout for switch off in the spin box."
#~ msgstr "Tukaj lahko nastavite časovno omejitev za izklop v vrtilnem polju."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Suspends the session after the selected time to the status "
#~ "<guilabel>Sleep</guilabel>, <guilabel>Hibernate</guilabel>, "
#~ "<guilabel>Shutdown</guilabel> or <guilabel>Lock screen</guilabel>."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Po izbranem času prekine sejo v stanje <guilabel>Spanje</guilabel>, "
#~ "<guilabel>Mirovanje</guilabel>, <guilabel>Izklop</guilabel> ali "
#~ "<guilabel>Zaklenjen zaslon</guilabel>."

#~ msgid "Button events handling"
#~ msgstr "Obravnava dogodkov gumbov"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Select actions to perform whenever the laptop lid is closed or a button "
#~ "is pressed."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Izberite dejanja, ki jih želite izvesti vsakič, ko zaprete pokrov "
#~ "prenosnika ali pritisnete gumb."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Activate this option to run a custom script when a profile is loaded, "
#~ "unloaded or after a given amount of time."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Aktivirajte to možnost, če želite zagnati skript po meri, ko je profil "
#~ "naložen, razložen ali po določenem času."

#~ msgid "<title>Activity Settings</title>"
#~ msgstr "<title>Nastavitve dejavnosti</title>"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Here you can configure the Power Management settings per activity. The "
#~ "settings for each activity can be configured on its own tab."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Tukaj lahko konfigurirate nastavitve upravljanja porabe energije za vsako "
#~ "dejavnost. Nastavitve za vsako dejavnost lahko konfigurirate na svojem "
#~ "zavihku."

#~ msgid "<screeninfo>Activity Settings</screeninfo>"
#~ msgstr "<screeninfo>Nastavitve dejavnosti</screeninfo>"

#~ msgid "<phrase>Activity Settings</phrase>"
#~ msgstr "<phrase>Nastavitve dejavnosti</phrase>"

#~ msgid "<para>Activity Settings</para>"
#~ msgstr "<para>Nastavitve dejavnosti</para>"

#~ msgid "Don't use special settings"
#~ msgstr "Ne uporabljajte posebnih nastavitev"

#~ msgid "Use the settings defined on <guilabel>Energy Saving</guilabel> page."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Uporabite nastavitve, določene na strani <guilabel>Varčevanje z energijo</"
#~ "guilabel>."

#~ msgid "Define a special behavior"
#~ msgstr "Določite posebno vedenje"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "If this option is chosen, a special behavior for activity can be chosen. "
#~ "If this is a presentation activity, you can check the <guilabel>Never "
#~ "shutdown the screen</guilabel> and <guilabel>Never shutdown the computer "
#~ "or let it go to sleep</guilabel> boxes."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Če izberete to možnost, lahko izberete posebno vedenje za dejavnost. Če "
#~ "je to predstavitvena dejavnost, lahko potrdite polja <guilabel>Nikoli ne "
#~ "izklopi zaslona</guilabel> in <guilabel>Nikoli ne izklopi računalnika in "
#~ "ga ne pusti, da preklopi v stanje spanja</guilabel>."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Here you can set the percentage after which the battery will be "
#~ "considered low."
#~ msgstr "Tukaj lahko nastavite odstotek, po katerem bo baterija prazna."

#~ msgid "Configure Notifications"
#~ msgstr "Konfigurirajte obvestila"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "If you want a deeper control over your notifications, you can refine them "
#~ "by clicking this button."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Če želite globlji nadzor nad svojimi obvestili, jih lahko izboljšate s "
#~ "klikom na ta gumb."
